[4] Prevention & false alarms

USA: Self-quarantine by missionary family, Arizona
--------------------------------------------------------
Date: 2 Oct 2014 An Arizona man who spent about 2 weeks in Liberia on a religious mission has quarantined himself and his family inside their Payson home, even though he is showing no signs of the Ebola virus. AM returned to the U.S. on Sun [28 Sep 2014]. He was checked for a fever -- as are all passengers -- before leaving Liberia, the African country being hit the hardest by the Ebola outbreak, and he said he is now checking his temperature twice daily. Fever is one of the 1st signs of Ebola. The self-imposed quarantine and twice-daily checks are just 2 of the precautions AM has taken before and after his trip with CrossWay International to distribute sanitation supplies and preach the gospel...
http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/10/02/man-quarantines-himself-family-after-trip-to-liberia/16620003

